  "texts": [
    "For instance, a platform might deploy a prototype AI labeler for likely disinformation under regulatory oversight, allowing for real-time learning and adjustment.",
    "Such experimentation can inform key design questions, such as acceptable error margins, redress mechanisms for false positives, and proportionality thresholds for intervention.",
    "These insights are crucial before formalizing policies into law.",
    "In parallel, the inclusion of sunset clauses and scheduled policy reviews should become a standard feature of AI-related legislation.",
    "Laws passed today may be obsolete within two years; thus, built-in review cycles (e.g., every 18-24 months) allow regulatory frameworks to evolve alongside technological progress."
  ],
